The instantGNU_ltdl is a sample program indicates how to use autoconf,
can be built on various Platforms(GNU Linux, msys, Mac OS X, etc).

1, To build the program, simply type:
  $ autoreconf -im;automake;./configure;make

2, you will get executable like this:
  main/.libs/autoconfsample.exe
  libraries/.libs/libShared.dll


This program ported from:
http://www.jaist.ac.jp/~kiyoshiy/memo/autoconf.html

you can get an original version from:
http://www.jaist.ac.jp/~kiyoshiy/memo/instantGNU_ltdl-1.1.tar.gz

